#data preprocessing
avg_balance = data %>% 
  group_by(account_id) %>% 
  summarise(average_balance = (max_balance + min_balance)/2)

have_loan = data %>% 
  select(account_id, loan_amount) %>% 
  mutate(loan_amount = replace(loan_amount, is.na(loan_amount) == FALSE, "T")) %>% 
  replace_na(list(loan_amount = "F")) %>%
  rename(have_loan = loan_amount)

have_credit = data %>% 
  select(account_id, credit_cards) %>% 
  mutate(credit_cards = replace(credit_cards, is.na(credit_cards) == FALSE, "T")) %>% 
  replace_na(list(credit_cards = "F")) %>%
  rename(have_credit = credit_cards)

data1 <- data %>% 
  inner_join(avg_balance, by = "account_id") %>% 
  inner_join(have_loan, by = "account_id")  %>% 
  inner_join(have_credit, by = "account_id")

Overall a big picture of the avarage balance with have/no credit card and have/no loan:

p <- ggplot(data1,aes(x=account_id,y=average_balance)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = have_credit, shape = have_loan)) +
  labs(title = "Average balance of accounts have/no credit card and have/no loan")
p

Since the points are all stack together, we seperate them in below graph.

p1 <- ggplot(data1,aes(x=account_id,y=average_balance)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = have_credit, shape = have_loan)) +
  facet_wrap(~have_loan,labeller=labeller(have_loan=c(T='have_loan',F='no_loan'))) +
  labs(title = "Average balance of accounts have/no credit card and have/no loan")
p1

We can see from above scatter plots that accounts with loan overall have a higher average balance.

p2 <- ggplot(data1,aes(x=average_balance,fill=have_credit)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=50,position="stack")+
  facet_wrap(~have_loan,labeller=labeller(have_loan=c(T='have_loan',F='no_loan')))+
  labs(title = "Distribution of Average balance for all accounts") +
  xlab('Average Balance') +
  ylab("Count")
p2

We can see from above histogram that the number of accounts that have no loan is much more than those have loan. The number of accounts that have no credit cards is also much more than those have credit cards. The average balance of most of accounts that have no loan distributed in the range of 0-45000. The average balance of accounts that have loan distributed relatively equally within the range of 15000 to 90000.
